reviews.text: This place wasn't exactly hot and not that crowded on a Saturday lunchtime. The more famous items here are Teochew fishball mee, soya bean, chicken rice, fa kueh.

8-10 minutes walk from Queenstown MTR station, not easily accessible and only one direct bus.
Take note some stalls do not operate on Weekend e. g. Amoy prawn noodles.
Favourite stalls expecting some queue and be patient.
Area was well kept, hygienic and airy.  Toilets collecting 10c??

I like it here ! Spacious and airy!  Braised Beef  noodles,prawn noodles x 2 ,LorMee x 2, fish ball noodles x3 ,mushroom horfun(sadly no more !) Chicken rice ×3 stalls are the famous stalls over here . Muslim mixed vegetables rice also nice !!!
Used to spend a lot of my time here as daughter's school is near by.
1st floor is their wet market selling meat ,chicken ,fish ,vegetables, fruits & condiments. 2nd floor is the hawker center.

Came down n saw a small queue for Ho Kee roasted saw Google is closed but they r open.
Aunty was friendly n nice. Thx for giving me lots of meat
Will drop by again to try others
Chicken rice full of bones from other stall

Lots of good food stalls such as Sin Kee Famous Chicken Rice, Amoy Street Boon Kee Prawn Noodle and Xin Lu Fishball. With new stall like HK Lung Hwa Chicken Rice • Noodle and more this food centre serves its residents and lunch crowd well.
